{"name":"alm_asset","description":"Manages the lifecycle of assets from procurement to retirement.","summary":"Sure! Here's a summary of the `alm_asset` object in ServiceNow:\n\n### `alm_asset` Object Summary\n\n**Object Name:** `alm_asset`\n\n**Purpose:**\nThe `alm_asset` object is used to manage and track assets within the Application Lifecycle Management (ALM) module of ServiceNow. It helps organizations keep an inventory of their software and hardware assets, monitor their usage, and manage their lifecycle.\n\n**Key Features:**\n1. **Asset Tracking:**\n   - Tracks both hardware and software assets.\n   - Includes details such as asset type, manufacturer, model, serial number, and location.\n\n2. **Lifecycle Management:**\n   - Manages the entire lifecycle of an asset from procurement to disposal.\n   - Tracks asset status, such as active, inactive, or retired.\n\n3. **Financial Management:**\n   - Records financial information related to assets, including purchase cost, depreciation, and warranty details.\n\n4. **Integration:**\n   - Integrates with other ServiceNow modules, such as Incident Management, Problem Management, and Change Management, to provide a comprehensive view of asset-related issues and changes.\n\n5. **Reporting and Analytics:**\n   - Provides reporting and analytics capabilities to help organizations make informed decisions about their asset management strategies.\n\n**Common Fields:**\n- `name`: The name of the asset.\n- `asset_tag`: A unique identifier for the asset.\n- `category`: The type of asset (e.g., hardware, software).\n- `manufacturer`: The manufacturer of the asset.\n- `model`: The model of the asset.\n- `serial_number`: The serial number of the asset.\n- `location`: The physical location of the asset.\n- `status`: The current status of the asset (e.g., active, inactive).\n- `purchase_date`: The date the asset was purchased.\n- `warranty_expiration`: The date the warranty expires.\n- `cost`: The purchase cost of the asset.\n\n**Us